</o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--></head><body lang=EN-US link=blue vlink=purple><div class=WordSection1><p class=MsoNormal>Hello openmpi-users,<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>A few weeks ago, I posted to the list about difficulties I was having getting openib to work with Torque (see &#8220;openib segfaults with Torque&#8221;, June 6, 2014). The issues were related to Torque imposing restrictive limits on locked memory, and have since been resolved.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>However, now that I&#8217;ve had some time to test the applications, I&#8217;m seeing abysmal performance over the openib layer. Applications run with the tcp btl execute about 10x faster than with the openib btl. Clearly something still isn&#8217;t quite right.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>I tried running with &#8220;-mca btl_openib_verbose 1&#8221;, but didn&#8217;t see anything resembling a smoking gun. How should I go about determining the source of the problem? (This uses the same OpenMPI Version 1.8.1 / SLES11 SP3 / GCC 4.8.3 setup discussed previously.)<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Thanks,<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Greg<o:p></o:p></p></div></body></html>
